<h2 class="text-xl font-light text-amber-600 dark:text-amber-400 mt-10 mb-4 border-l-4 border-amber-400 pl-4">Strategy Tips</h2>

<div class="not-prose my-6 grid grid-cols-1 gap-4">
  <div class="p-4 rounded-xl border border-purple-500/30 bg-purple-950/20 hover:border-purple-400 transition-colors">
    <p class="text-sm text-gray-300"><span class="text-purple-400 font-semibold">Prepend to verbs:</span> Almost any verb on the board can take MIS- in front. LEAD→MISLEAD, FIRE→MISFIRE, TAKE→MISTAKE. Scan for verbs near the left edge and capitalise on the extension.</p>
  </div>
  <div class="p-4 rounded-xl border border-purple-500/30 bg-purple-950/20 hover:border-purple-400 transition-colors">
    <p class="text-sm text-gray-300"><span class="text-purple-400 font-semibold">M on premium squares:</span> Position M on a double letter score for 6 points from that single tile, then build the rest of MIS- outward. The 3-point M value compounds beautifully with premium squares.</p>
  </div>
  <div class="p-4 rounded-xl border border-purple-500/30 bg-purple-950/20 hover:border-purple-400 transition-colors">
    <p class="text-sm text-gray-300"><span class="text-purple-400 font-semibold">Bingo with Q words:</span> MISQUOTE and MISQUOTED are valuable bingo targets. If you hold M-I-S plus Q-U, you only need two more tiles for a 50-point bonus play.</p>
